Illustrating the complexity of recombination processes, it has been observed that the kinetic profiles usually depend on experimental parameters such as the laser pulse intensity or the semiconductor’s particle size. These parameters define the average number of photogenerated charge carriers per particle. Serpone et al. [20] analyzed colloidal TiO2 sols and observed that, when the average number of electron–hole pairs per particle was lower than ~ 0.5, the decays followed first-order kinetics:5c=ct=0e-krt.\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
